    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "**Missed counts.** Across all 5 subjects with pairwise-unmixing data,\n",
    "13.8–27.7 % of GT-matched HCR ROIs are absent from\n",
    "`unmixed_all_cells.csv`. The newly added 790322 sits in the\n",
    "spot-subject regime: **23.3 %** dropped (181 / 778). The two\n",
    "intensity-panel subjects (755252, 767022) drop fewer cells overall\n",
    "(~14 %); the four spot-panel subjects (782149, 788406, 790322 plus\n",
    "755252's panel partner 767022 that has missing metrics.pickle)\n",
    "drop 23–28 %.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quality of missed cells.** The dropped cells are not low-quality\n",
    "ROIs being filtered. The v5d binary score (P(good ∪ bad_ok)) is\n",
    "high on the missed subset:\n",
    "\n",
    "- median ≥ 0.85 on every subject;\n",
    "- 95–96 % of missed cells score ≥ 0.5 on **788406** and **790322**;\n",
    "- 83 % on 782149, 79 % on 767022, 67 % on 755252.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Argmax class breakdown (missed cells).** 81–88 % of missed cells\n",
    "on 782149/788406/790322 land on argmax = `good`; the missed pool\n",
    "on those subjects contains only 4–11 % `bad`. By contrast, missed\n",
    "cells on 755252 and 767022 contain a higher fraction of `bad`\n",
    "(23 % / 16 %) — those losses are at least partly quality-aware.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Kept-vs-missed comparison.** The argmax-positive (`good ∪ bad_ok`)\n",
    "rate is similar between kept and missed for the spot subjects\n",
    "(both ≥ 87 % on 782149, ≥ 95 % on 788406, ≥ 92 % on 790322),\n",
    "confirming that the unmixing drop is not selecting for a\n",
    "distinguishable quality signature on those subjects.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Depth.** The missed-cell histogram broadly tracks the kept-cell\n",
    "depth distribution on every subject — there is no obvious\n",
    "depth-specific concentration of dropped cells, so the unmixing\n",
    "filter is not a pure depth gate either.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Implication.** ~23–28 % of validated GFP+ cells silently\n",
    "disappear from the spot-panel unmixed CSVs, the dropped cells\n",
    "look like high-quality ROIs by the v5d classifier, and they are\n",
    "not concentrated at any particular depth. Whatever criterion the\n",
    "unmixing pipeline applies for retention is not aligned with ROI\n",
    "segmentation quality, with depth, or with the GT-matched validity\n",
    "of the cells."
